The paper deals with trajectory optimization for a quadrotor system, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The focus is on observability of the system states, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of GPS-IMU sensors, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications. Finally, the paper proposes a method for optimizing trajectories, which involves reasoning and decision-making, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
